\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie stepped off the ferry, the lingering scent of salt and fish clinging to his coat as he pedaled back through the familiar streets of Weshaven. The town moved at its usual pace\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 fishermen hauling in their morning catches, merchants calling out their wares, the rhythmic hammering of shipwrights at work. It felt routine, but his thoughts still lingered on Osthaven, on Aella, on the emblem of the owl perched on a scroll.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 By the time he reached the apothecary, the comforting scent of herbs and simmering potions greeted him like an old friend. He pushed open the wooden door and stepped into the brewing room, where golden light streamed through the lofty windows, casting long, shifting shadows.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 A deep but gentle voice called out from the far end of the room, its warmth filling the space like the heat of a hearth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Morning, Edward!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Markus stood hunched over his workstation, his broad frame making the desk seem almost too small for him. His wild curls peeked out from under his cap, and a faint flush colored his round cheeks\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 likely from standing over boiling cauldrons all morning. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He was a large presence in every sense, but his movements were measured, careful, and full of practiced ease as he stirred a simmering mixture, his huge hands treating delicate ingredients with surprising gentleness.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie smirked and reached into his satchel. "Got you something."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Markus glanced up, his dark eyes curious as Eddie handed over a small paper bag. A familiar scent wafted from within.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "You didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t," Markus breathed, opening the bag to reveal golden-brown roasted chestnuts. His expression flickered between delight and nostalgia.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Stopped by the old stall," Eddie said. "Figured you\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d appreciate it."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "You really do know how to make a guy\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s morning." }{\f3\fs24\b0\i0 Markus chuckled, popping one into his mouth and sighing contentedly. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "So, how\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d it go? With Torrie, I mean."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Good. Aella still looks like Aella." Eddie exhaled, glancing past Markus as if he could still see the academy in the distance. "Nothing much has changed since we were there."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Markus hummed, a small smile tugging at his lips. "I bet she was buzzing with excitement."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "Practically skipping through the gates," Eddie admitted with a chuckle.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Markus laughed, shaking his head. "Yeah, that sounds about right." He rolled up his sleeves, returning his focus to the potion before him. "She\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s gonna do great there, you know. Always knew she had it in her."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t respond immediately, just nodded, watching the steam rise from Markus\u8217\'92s cauldron.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 For a moment, it was like old times.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie had just popped a chestnut into his mouth when Markus spoke, his voice casual but laced with meaning.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, by the way\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Mr. Welton wants to see you earlier.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Eddie froze mid-chew. A slow, creeping realization dawned on him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He was supposed to hand over the formula today.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Damn it\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 I forgot!\u8221\'94 He shot upright, }{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  swallowed hard, nearly choking.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  nearly knocking over a stack of parchment on the counter.}
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah, figured.\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Markus raised an amused brow, still munching on his snack. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93He\u8217\'92s already up at the tower.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Cursing under his breath, Eddie spun on his heel and bolted toward the stairs. His boots thudded against the wooden steps as he rushed to his desk, rummaging through scattered notes, ink-stained pages, and unfinished drafts. Where the hell was it?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He shoved aside a worn-out alchemy textbook, and there it was\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the carefully scribed formula, buried beneath a pile of old scribbles.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Snatching it up, he didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t waste another second. He turned on his heel and sprinted towards the tower, heart pounding.}}